subSubSection.paragraph:
Abdomen:
Green, with or without rounded marks on the first five tergites; apodema of tergite 9 + ectoproct strongly sclerotized and with ventral projection below the base of the 
callus cerci
, apex of this projection dilated at the ventral extremity; lateral genital atrium without scales field (
Figs. 9–10
). 
Male genitalia:
gonarcus very wide, square-shaped, dorsomedial hood wider than long with acute apex (
Figs. 11– 12
); lateral arms not projected above the arc; two dorsolaterally inflated gonocornua of irregular margin projected posteriorly from gonarcus (
Figs. 13–14
); arcessus membranous, basally with two dorsal inflated, horn-shaped lobes or processes, apex ventrally directed and laterally lobulated (
Fig. 14
); gonosaccus with long gonosetae; gonocristae present. Gonapsis elongated and flattened, dilated and bifurcated apically (
Fig. 15
).

Female genitalia:
Bursa copulatrix long and narrow, with many folds (
Fig. 16
); Subgenitalia longer than wide (
Fig. 17
); spermatheca elongated with posterior extremity curved in J-shape, spermathecal gland long (
Fig. 18
).
